% Lore local da geracao 7
% Formato: pokemon_lore(ID, Texto).
:- multifile pokemon_lore/2.
pokemon_lore(722, 'It sends its feathers, which are as sharp as blades, flying in attack. Its legs are strong, so its kicks are also formidable.').
pokemon_lore(723, 'This narcissistic Pokémon is a clean freak. If you don’t groom it diligently, it will stop listening to you.').
pokemon_lore(724, 'It nocks its arrow quills and shoots them at opponents. When it simply can’t afford to miss, it tugs the vine on its head to improve its focus.').
pokemon_lore(725, 'If you try too hard to get close to it, it won’t open up to you. Even if you do grow close, giving it too much affection is still a no-no.').
pokemon_lore(726, 'It can act spoiled if it grows close to its Trainer. A powerful Pokémon, its sharp claws can leave its Trainer’s whole body covered in scratches.').
pokemon_lore(727, 'Although it’s rough mannered and egotistical, it finds beating down unworthy opponents boring. It gets motivated for stronger opponents.').
pokemon_lore(728, 'The balloons it inflates with its nose grow larger and larger as it practices day by day.').
pokemon_lore(729, 'It gets excited when it sees a dance it doesn’t know. This hard worker practices diligently until it can learn that dance.').
pokemon_lore(730, 'To Primarina, every battle is a stage. It takes down its prey with beautiful singing and dancing.').
pokemon_lore(731, 'It pecks at trees with its hard beak. You can get some idea of its mood or condition from the rhythm of its pecking.').
pokemon_lore(732, 'It can bend the tip of its beak to produce over a hundred different cries at will.').
pokemon_lore(733, 'They smack beaks with others of their kind to communicate. The strength and number of hits tell each other how they feel.').
pokemon_lore(734, 'Its stomach takes up most of its long torso. It’s a big eater, so the amount Trainers have to spend on its food is no laughing matter.').
pokemon_lore(735, 'Although it wasn’t originally found in Alola, this Pokémon was brought over a long time ago when there was a huge Rattata outbreak.').
pokemon_lore(736, 'If you find its nest, you shouldn’t stick your hand inside. You’ll get bitten by an irritated Grubbin.').
pokemon_lore(737, 'It buries itself in fallen leaves and barely moves, munching away on humus. If you accidentally step on one, you’ll get a shock!').
pokemon_lore(738, 'It has an organ that generates electricity in its abdomen. It concentrates energy in its strong jaws and fires off powerful jolts of electricity.').
pokemon_lore(739, 'Its hard pincers are well suited to both offense and defense. Fights between two Crabrawler are like boxing matches.').
pokemon_lore(740, 'It stores coldness in its pincers and pummels its foes. It can even smash thick walls of ice to bits!').
pokemon_lore(741, 'It wins the hearts of its enemies with its passionate dancing and then uses the opening it creates to burn them up with blazing flames.').
pokemon_lore(742, 'Nectar and pollen are its favorite fare. In fields of flowers, it gets into skirmishes with Butterfree over food.').
pokemon_lore(743, 'Rain makes pollen damp, so Ribombee hates rain. When it sees ominous clouds, it finds a hollow in a tree, where it waits stock-still.').
pokemon_lore(744, 'As they develop, their disposition grows more violent and aggressive. Many Trainers find them too much to handle and abandon them.').
pokemon_lore(745, 'The sharp rocks in its mane can cut like knives. Lycanroc wears its prey down by degrees before finishing them off.').
pokemon_lore(746, 'They’re weak, so they move in schools. However, they can also often be seen all alone, having strayed from the school.').
pokemon_lore(747, 'They eat Corsola branches, so Mareanie are hated by craftsmen who work with Corsola branches that have naturally fallen off.').
pokemon_lore(748, 'To attack, this Pokémon sends toxic spikes flying at its enemies. Ones that come close get mown down by the claws on its feet.').
pokemon_lore(749, 'It loves playing in the mud. If it isn’t showered with mud on a daily basis, it gets stressed out and stops listening to its Trainer.').
pokemon_lore(750, 'It remains calm and unmoving no matter the situation. It mixes dirt with the saliva in its mouth to make a special kind of mud.').
pokemon_lore(751, 'When two Dewpider meet, they display their water bubbles to each other. Then the one with the smaller bubble gets out of the other’s way.').
pokemon_lore(752, 'It usually passes its time in the water. When its belly is full, it stores its subdued prey in the water bubble on its head.').
pokemon_lore(753, 'When the sun rises, Fomantis spreads its four leaves and bathes in the sunlight. The tip of its head has a pleasant aroma.').
pokemon_lore(754, 'For self-protection, it pretends to be a bug Pokémon. Both of its arms bear keen-edged petals.').
pokemon_lore(755, 'It scatters its shining spores around itself. Even though they’re dangerous, nighttime tours of forests where Morelull live are popular.').
pokemon_lore(756, 'It puts its prey to sleep and siphons off their vitality through the tip of its arms. If one of its kind is weakened, it helps by sending it vitality.').
pokemon_lore(757, 'The males will do whatever the females tell them. They give the females most of their food. Due to malnutrition, the males can’t evolve.').
pokemon_lore(758, 'Salazzle lives deep in caves and forces the Salandit it has attracted with its pheromones to serve it.').
pokemon_lore(759, 'It boasts power enough to split large trees in half. The organ on its rear releases an odor that it uses to communicate with others of its kind.').
pokemon_lore(760, 'It waves its hands wildly in intimidation and warning. Life is over for anyone who doesn’t run away as fast as possible.').
pokemon_lore(761, 'Because of its sweet, delicious aroma, bird Pokémon are always after it, but it’s not intelligent enough to care.').
pokemon_lore(762, 'It’s protected by its hard sepals, so it plays with bird Pokémon without worry. They peck it relentlessly, but it doesn’t care.').
pokemon_lore(763, 'A master of grand and beautiful kicks, it can knock out even kickboxing champions with a single blow.').
pokemon_lore(764, 'It stretches sticky vines out from its head and picks flowers to adorn itself with. When it doesn’t have any flowers, it feels uneasy.').
pokemon_lore(765, 'It normally spends its time meditating in the treetops. It throws Poké Balls and gives other Pokémon orders as it pleases.').
pokemon_lore(766, 'They use their saliva to stick leaves to their shoulders. You can tell what troop they belong to from the position of the leaves.').
pokemon_lore(767, 'It will pick up anything it finds on the ground. Sometimes it finds coins, so Murkrow and Meowth will go after it.').
pokemon_lore(768, 'The shell covering its body is as hard as diamond. This Pokémon will do anything it takes to win.').
pokemon_lore(769, 'It likes the shovel on its head, so Sandygast will get serious and fight any children who come to take it back.').
pokemon_lore(770, 'Each of its grains of sand has its own will. Palossand eats small Pokémon and siphons away their vital essence while they’re still alive.').
pokemon_lore(771, 'The tradition known as Pyukumuku chucking started from the custom of throwing Pyukumuku back into the sea after they wash onshore.').
pokemon_lore(772, 'A Pokémon weapon developed for a specific mission, it went berserk during an experiment, so it was cryogenically frozen.').
pokemon_lore(773, 'This is its form once it has awakened and evolved. Freed from its heavy mask, its speed is greatly increased.').
pokemon_lore(774, 'It lives in the ozone layer, where it becomes food for stronger Pokémon. When it tries to run away, it falls to the ground.').
pokemon_lore(775, 'It stays asleep from the moment it’s born. When it falls into a deep sleep, it stops moving altogether.').
pokemon_lore(776, 'It lives in volcanoes and eats sulfur and other minerals. Materials from the food it eats form the basis of its explosive shell.').
pokemon_lore(777, 'When it’s surprised or agitated, the 14 fur spikes on its back will stand up involuntarily.').
pokemon_lore(778, 'Although it’s a quiet, lonely Pokémon, if you try to look at what’s under its rag, it will become agitated and resist violently.').
pokemon_lore(779, 'It burrows beneath the sand, radiating psychic power from the protuberance on its head. It waits for prey as it surveys the area.').
pokemon_lore(780, 'If a child it has made friends with is bullied, Drampa will find the bully’s house and burn it to the ground.').
pokemon_lore(781, 'It wraps its prey in green seaweed and sucks away their vitality. It only likes to go after big prey like Wailord.').
pokemon_lore(782, 'It smacks the scales on its head against rocks or against the ground to frighten its opponents. It can also contact its friends with these noises.').
pokemon_lore(783, 'It makes noise by clanging its scales together. When the rhythm has reached its peak, Hakamo-o attacks.').
pokemon_lore(784, 'When it howls after finishing off its prey, the metallic sounds of its celebrating comrades can be heard from all around.').
pokemon_lore(785, 'Although it’s called a guardian deity, if a person or Pokémon puts it in a bad mood, it will become a malevolent deity and attack.').
pokemon_lore(786, 'It heals the wounds of people and Pokémon by sprinkling them with its sparkling scales. This guardian deity is worshiped on Akala.').
pokemon_lore(787, 'Although it’s called a guardian deity, it’s violent enough to crush anyone it sees as an enemy.').
pokemon_lore(788, 'This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog, it came to be both feared and revered.').
pokemon_lore(789, 'Even though its helpless, gaseous body can be blown away by the slightest breeze, it doesn’t seem to care.').
pokemon_lore(790, 'The king who ruled Alola in times of antiquity called it the “cocoon of the stars” and built an altar to worship it.').
pokemon_lore(791, 'Sometimes the result of its opening an Ultra Wormhole is that energy and life-forms from other worlds are called here to this world.').
pokemon_lore(792, 'Records of it exist in writings from long, long ago, where it was known by the name “the beast that calls the moon.”').
pokemon_lore(793, 'A life-form from another world, it was dubbed a UB and is thought to produce a strong neurotoxin.').
pokemon_lore(794, 'Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.').
pokemon_lore(795, 'A life-form that lives in another world, its body is thin and supple, but it also possesses great power.').
pokemon_lore(796, 'Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.').
pokemon_lore(797, 'One of the dangerous UBs, high energy readings can be detected coming from both of its huge arms.').
pokemon_lore(798, 'This Ultra Beast’s body, which is as thin as paper, is like a sharpened sword.').
pokemon_lore(799, 'Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.').
pokemon_lore(800, 'It looks somehow pained as it rages around in search of light, which serves as its energy. It’s apparently from another world.').
pokemon_lore(801, 'It synchronizes its consciousness with others to understand their feelings. This faculty makes it useful for taking care of people.').
pokemon_lore(802, 'It slips into the shadows of others and mimics their powers and movements. As it improves, it becomes stronger than those it’s imitating.').
pokemon_lore(803, 'This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.').
pokemon_lore(804, 'It stores hundreds of liters of poisonous liquid inside its body. It is one of the organisms known as UBs.').
pokemon_lore(805, 'It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.').
pokemon_lore(806, 'It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the explosion of its own head. It’s apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.').
pokemon_lore(807, 'It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack, they’ll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.').
pokemon_lore(808, 'It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.').
pokemon_lore(809, 'Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.').
